          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB",
                "EDEG",
                "GSPEC",
                "MOSEP",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two stacks were",
                "irradiated at the external beam line of the CGR90",
                "cyclotron in Louvain la Neuve (LLN, Belgium) with",
                "deuterons of 50 MeV incident energy. In exp1, foils",
                "were stacked in a 18 times repeated Al-Ti-C-Ti. The",
                "Ti foils (10.9 mm thick) also serves as catcher foils",
                "for the recoiled reaction products. In exp2 the stack",
                "contained beside the carbon foils also Al (49.06 um),",
                "Ti (10.9 um), Ni (9.95 um) and Mg (275 um) foils. The",
                "irradiation took place under vacuum. The beam current",
                "was constant at about 120 nA during the 1.5 h",
                "irradiation. The cross-sections were calculated using",
                "the activation formula. The decay data taken from the",
                "on-line data library NuDat2 based on Evaluated",
                "Nuclear Structure Data File (ENSDF), Database version",
                "of October 2011.",
                "Care was taken to correct the 7Be cross-section",
                "measured directly for recoiled fragments."
              ]
            }
          ],
